{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"556014f2-2227-43f2-a7da-6e6567a20139","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`**\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`**\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`**\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet --version` to confirm the SDK, then `dotnet build` to check for any breaking API changes. Review the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) for any breaking changes relevant to your dependencies.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2a9825f7-5fe5-4f60-89a6-b24848c31d02","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward knowledge question — I don't need to explore any codebase. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":266},"id":"ffdd99c0-1902-48c7-a4c0-ca713ed23026","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:01:41.388Z","parentId":"2a59a75e-128d-41f6-8415-da17237c192a"}
